## Confirm device identity on-device (run once per unit)

```bash
# Chipset / platform — feeds the HTP arch decision
adb shell getprop ro.board.platform      # S22+: taro ; S26: read & record
adb shell getprop ro.hardware            # expect qcom on Snapdragon units
adb shell getprop ro.soc.model           # e.g. SM8450 (S22+)

# Sanity: Exynos units will show exynos / s5e here -> WRONG path, stop
adb shell getprop ro.board.platform | grep -qi exynos && echo "EXYNOS - no QNN path"
```

If `ro.board.platform` returns an `exynos`/`s5e*` value, this device cannot use
the QNN/Hexagon pipeline. Stop and either get a Snapdragon unit or switch to the
LiteRT/NNAPI fallback track.

