## Thermal test (run early on every device)

The sustained-load test is the decisive benchmark — it's where the S22+ shows its
ceiling and where the Ultra justifies itself.

```bash
# 10-minute sustained NPU loop; capture FPS + thermal/clock decay
adb shell "cd /data/local/tmp && qnn-net-run \
  --backend libQnnHtp.so --retrieve_context yolo11n_htp.bin \
  --input_list input_list.txt --num_inferences 20000 \
  --profiling_level detailed --output_dir out_sustained/"
# then: parse_profile.py out_sustained/  -> p50/p99 latency + FPS-over-time curve
```

Record for each device: cold-start FPS, FPS after 10 min, and the throttle knee
time. The deployment decision (S26+ vs Ultra) should be made on the **post-throttle
sustained FPS**, not the cold peak.

